itemLabel: Prince William Frederick, Duke of Gloucester and Edinburgh
itemDescription: (1776-1834); British prince, nephew and son-in-law of George III

wikipedia_page.main: Prince William Frederick, Duke of Gloucester and Edinburgh,  (15 January 1776 – 30 November 1834) was a great-grandson of King George II and nephew and son-in-law of King George III of the United Kingdom.
